article.headline: Moore scores 27, Saint Bonaventure downs Canisius 87-78
article.description: — Chance Moore had 27 points in Saint Bonaventure's 87-78 win over Canisius on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Moore scores 27, Saint Bonaventure downs Canisius 87-78
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Chance Moore had 27 points in Saint Bonaventure's 87-78 win over Canisius on Saturday night. Moore added six rebounds and three blocks for the Bonnies (2-0). Melvin Council Jr. scored 17 points, going 5 of 13 from the floor, including 1 for 5 from 3-point range, and 6 for 7 from the line. Dasonte Bowen shot 4 of 8 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 12 points. Paul McMillan IV led the Golden Griffins (0-2) in scoring, finishing with 31 points. Tana Kopa added 19 points for Canisius. Dylan Godfrey had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
